article.headline: Obaze, Ford lead way for Lady Techsters
article.linkText: LaTech dumps Fresno State for 10th straight victory
article.story:
FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Amber Obaze scored 22 points, and Cheryl
Ford had 18 rebounds and 11 points to lead Louisiana Tech (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) to
its 10th straight victory, 63-53 over Fresno State on Saturday.

	   Erica Smith scored 13 points, and Trina Frierson had 11 points
and seven rebounds to help Louisiana Tech (12-2, 5-0 WAC) extend
its winning streak on the same day Connecticut broke the Lady
Techsters' NCAA record of 54 straight victories, set from 1980-82.

	   Louisiana Tech is unbeaten since a Dec. 4 home loss to
Tennessee.

	   Omelogo Udeze had 18 points and 12 rebounds for the Bulldogs
(9-7, 3-3). She hit two free throws with 12:09 left to give Fresno
State a one-point lead, but the Lady Techsters countered with a
12-1 run.

	   Fresno State coach Stacy Johnson-Klein, who has made the
once-moribund Bulldogs competitive in her first season, spent the
past two seasons as an assistant to former coach Leon Barmore at
Louisiana Tech.
